    <section ids="google-cloud-storage-backup-driver" names="google\ cloud\ storage\ backup\ driver">
        <title>Google Cloud Storage backup driver</title>
        <paragraph>The Google Cloud Storage (GCS) backup driver backs up volumes of any type to
            Google Cloud Storage.</paragraph>
        <paragraph>To enable the GCS backup driver, include the following option in the
            <literal>cinder.conf</literal> file:</paragraph>
        <literal_block highlight_args="{}" language="ini" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">backup_driver = cinder.backup.drivers.google</literal_block>
        <paragraph>The following configuration options are available for the GCS backup
            driver.</paragraph>
